<h4>Carers <span class="error">Is this still the case?</span></h4><p><strong>The Plough Hotel & Restaurant</strong><br>The Plough has opened a communal room for carers in the community. The room includes a fridge, microwave, toaster, kettle etc. and allows them to take breaks there and utilise the shower and toilet facilities.</p><p>If anyone is aware of local carers in the Llandeilo and Manordeilo & Salem areas that would find this useful then please get in touch with The Plough on 01558 823431 so that they can make the necessary arrangements.</p><hr><h4>Carmarthenshire County Council</h4><p>The County Council has a useful hub of information for residents and businesses with all kinds of news, support, and links to community organisations. <a href="http://newsroom.carmarthenshire.gov.wales/">Please visit their website</a> for more information.</p><p>Six area teams have been set up to provide assistance and support, building on work already being carried out in our communities, with council staff helping volunteers on the ground.</p><p>Each area team includes dedicated officers and vehicles to help support people who are unable to access food delivery services, or those suffering from hardship and live in an area not covered by a foodbank.</p><p>They also assist local shops with grocery deliveries for those who are self-isolating.</p><p>In addition, they are the main point of contact for town and community councils. The Area Teams are also working closely with CAVS in relation to supporting volunteers. Please contact your area team if you need more volunteers.</p><p>The area teams are:</p><dl><dt>AREA 1 - <a href="mailto:covid19area1@carmarthenshire.gov.uk">covid19area1@carmarthenshire.gov.uk</a></dt><dd>Carmarthen Town North, Carmarthen Town South, Carmarthen Town West, Llanboidy, St Clears, Laugharne, Whitland, Llansteffan</dd><dt>AREA 2 - <a href="mailto:covid19area2@carmarthenshire.gov.uk">covid19area2@carmarthenshire.gov.uk</a></dt><dd>Cynwyl Elfed, Cenarth, Llanfihangel ar arth, Trelech, Llangeler, Llanybydder, Llanllwni</dd><dt>AREA 3 - <a href="mailto:covid19area3@carmarthenshire.gov.uk">covid19area3@carmarthenshire.gov.uk</a></dt><dd>Abergwili, St Ishmael Llanddarog, Llanegwad, Llanfihangel Aberbythych, Llangunnor, Llangyndeyrn</dd><dt>AREA 4 - <a href="mailto:covid19area4@carmarthenshire.gov.uk">covid19area4@carmarthenshire.gov.uk</a></dt><dd>Llanelli rural, Llanelli town, Llangennech, Pembrey & Burry port, Trimsaran</dd><dt>AREA 5 - <a href="mailto:covid19area5@carmarthenshire.gov.uk">covid19area5@carmarthenshire.gov.uk</a></dt><dd>Pontamman, Ammanford, Betws, Cwarter Bach, Glanamman, Garnant, Gorslas, Pontyberem, Llannon, Hendy, Llandybie</dd><dt>AREA 6 - <a href="mailto:covid19area6@carmarthenshire.gov.uk">covid19area6@carmarthenshire.gov.uk</a></dt><dd>Manordeilo & Salem, Llangadog, Llandovery, Llandeilo, Cynwyl Gaeo, Cilycwm</dd></dl><h4>Llandeilo Covid-19 Community Support Group</h4><p>This group was created to set up a network of Llandeilo residents to help those around them stuck in isolation</p><ul><li>Website: <a href="https://llandeilocovid19.com/">https://llandeilocovid19.com/</a></li><li>Facebook: <a href="http://www.facebook.com/groups/196451478462428">www.facebook.com/groups/196451478462428</a></li><li>Email: <a href="mailto:llandeilocovid19@mail.com">llandeilocovid19@mail.com</a></li><li>Phone: 07395 949914</li></ul><h4>Salem Covid-19 Mutual Aid Group</h4><p>We have also set up a local support group which now has around 50 people in the Facebook group and around 25 volunteers on the list ready to help.</p><p>Please don't hesitate to contact us if you need help:</p><ul><li>Shopping</li><li>Picking up Prescriptions</li><li>Urgent supplies</li><li>Posting mail</li><li>Checking youâ€™re OK</li></ul><ul><li>Facebook: <a href="http://www.facebook.com/groups/SalemMutualAidGroup/">www.facebook.com/groups/SalemMutualAidGroup/</a></li><li>Email: <a href="mailto:salemvillagecarms@yahoo.co.uk">salemvillagecarms@yahoo.co.uk</a></li><li>Phone - 01558 822875 Karen and Andrew Goss / 07891 592428 Community Councillor Owen Williams</li></ul><h4>Welsh Government</h4><p>The Welsh Government is issuing weekly bulletins on the coronavirus (COVID-19) which our residents may find useful. Please consider signing up to the bulletin so that you can be sure to receive these on a weekly basis.</p><p>If you would like to receive the coronavirus bulletin <a href="https://public.govdelivery.com/accounts/UKWALES/subscriber/new?topic_id=UKWALES_197">please sign up here</a> or email <a href="mailto:cabinetcommunications@gov.wales">cabinetcommunications@gov.wales</a></p><h4>Public Health Wales</h4><p>There is now a single place on the Public Health Wales website where all the <a href="https://phw.nhs.wales/topics/latest-information-on-novel-coronavirus-covid-19/coronavirus-resources/easy-read-resources/">Easy Read versions of COVID-19 guidance</a> are available in both English and Welsh versions <span class="error">These are (very) out of date!</span>.</p><h4>Age Cymru - Check in and Chat Service for over 70s</h4><p>Reassurance for older people, answer basic queries and link people to local services and support during the Coronavirus outbreak. 08000 223 444 <a href="mailto:enquiries@agecymru.org.uk">enquiries@agecymru.org.uk</a> <a href="http://bit.ly/CheckInAndChat">http://bit.ly/CheckInAndChat</a></p><p>Carmarthenshire County Council round up of Local Support for all: (select Llandeilo): <a href="http://newsroom.carmarthenshire.gov.wales/2020/02/community-support/">http://newsroom.carmarthenshire.gov.wales/2020/02/community-support/</a></p>